18/05/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EULEX announced the arrest of a Kosovo Serb outside Zubin Potok, for suspected involvement in organised crime. 
According to a EULEX press release, Jevro Pantelic was arrested as part of an investigation related to organised crime, money laundering, fuel smuggling, tax evasion and evasion of import duty and excise tax. 
Interior Minister Bajram Rexhepi said that all criminals will be arrested sooner or later, irrespective of where they are, including in Kosovo north. 
(RTK, TV 21, Kohavision, Klan Kosova - 17/05/11)
